sbml2modelica.preprocessing

Class EventPreprocessingManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.PreprocessingManager
      • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.EventPreprocessingManager

  • public class EventPreprocessingManager
extends PreprocessingManager
    The EventPreprocessingManager performs a series of operations to ensure that the Events in the Model are in a certain standard form.
    Such standard form impose that no math attribute is missing from any component of the Event and that the Trigger exists.

    • Method Detail

      • preprocessTrigger

        public void preprocessTrigger(org.sbml.jsbml.Event e)
        This method applies the pre-processing operation to the Trigger of the given Event.
        In particular, the Trigger must exists and its math attribute must be set. If the Trigger does not exists, then it is created. If its math attribute is not set, it is set to false.
        Parameters:
        e - The Event to pre-process.

      • preprocessDelay

        public void preprocessDelay(org.sbml.jsbml.Event e)
        This method applies the pre-processing operation to the Delay of the given Event.
        In particular, the Delay could not exists, but if it exists, then its math attribute must be set. If its math attribute is not set, the Delay is removed.
        Parameters:
        e - The Event to pre-process.

      • preprocessPriority

        public void preprocessPriority(org.sbml.jsbml.Event e)
        This method applies the pre-processing operation to the Priority of the given Event.
        In particular, the Priority could not exists, but if it exists, then its math attribute must be set. If its math attribute is not set, the Priority is removed.
        Parameters:
        e - The Event to pre-process.

      • preprocessAssignments

        public void preprocessAssignments(org.sbml.jsbml.Event e)
        This method applies the pre-processing operation to each EventAssignment in the given Event.
        In particular, each EventAssignment with a no set math attribute is removed from the list of EventAssignments of the Event.
        Parameters:
        e - The Event to pre-process.

      • preprocessEvents

        public void preprocessEvents()
        This method applies the pre-processing operation to each Event in the Model.
        The pre-processing operation involves the following:
        • Adding a Trigger to an Event, if it has not one.
        • Adding the math attribute to a Trigger, if it has not one set.
        • Removing a Delay from an Event, if it has no set math attribute.
        • Removing a Priority from an Event, if it has no set math attribute.
        • Removing an EventAssignment from an Event, if it has no set math attribute.
